com.hexoskin.resp_drift_correction

Class Corrector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hexoskin.resp_drift_correction.Corrector

  • public class Corrector
extends java.lang.Object
    Respiration Corrector It is important to use one corrector per hexoskin. If you switches hexoskin devices you will need to destroy this corrector and to create a new one. You can definitely use the same instance but be sure to call uninit then init to reinitialize the corrector.

      • setRespCoefficientFromMaxExpiredVolume

        public long setRespCoefficientFromMaxExpiredVolume(long timestamp,
                                                   double volume)

        Function to update resp coefficient from an expired volume. The function calculate device maximal expiration in the last 5 minutes and from the given volume to set the respiration coefficient.

        scenario =>

        • record for 2 minute then at minute 2 do a maximal expiration.
        • At minute 4 say that you did a maximal expiration at minute 2.
        • The function return 1.5 min saying that the end on the maximal expiration was found at 1.5 min
        Parameters:
        timestamp - approximative hexotimestamp of the max volume expired
        volume - volume expired measured from an external device: in liter
        Returns:
        • timestamp of the end of the maximal expiration detected
        • -1 => There was less that 1 insp-exp timestamp stores close to the given timestamp
        • -2 => Detected volume by the device was too small
        • -3 => Specified volume was not between 1 and 10
        • -4 => Corrected buffer not accumulated yet. retry in 5 sec
        • -5 => Disconnected time found in the last 5 min
